
* UART

//CABLE COLOUR LABEL

- Green: RX(reciever)
- White: TX(transmitter)
- Black: GND(Ground)
- Red: VCC(not_connected)

#link to see the pin configuration(laballing) on the raspberry pi
https://pinout.xyz/pinout/uart
https://www.jeffgeerling.com/blog/2021/attaching-raspberry-pis-serial-console-uart-debugging
https://medium.com/@sarala.saraswati/connecting-to-your-raspberry-pi-console-via-the-serial-cable-44d7df95f03e

#Now connect the uart cable and find uart port location
ls /dev/tty

ls /dev/tty<usb/port/location> 115200 -fn
